150
00:26:39.930 --> 00:26:46.349
Nico Flaig: to do at the fore, but just curious if ELs can take a look at this, and…

151
00:26:46.590 --> 00:26:48.989
Nico Flaig: Yeah, just think about how that could work.

152
00:26:52.580 --> 00:26:55.560
dan (danceratopz): That's a good point, Nico, thank you very much. Does…

153
00:26:55.770 --> 00:27:01.900
dan (danceratopz): Someone have an answer on the spot for that now, or any… any thoughts on that that they want to bring up?

154
00:27:07.330 --> 00:27:12.590
dan (danceratopz): Okay, then that's definitely something we can pick up for ACDE on Thursday.

155
00:27:12.920 --> 00:27:22.769
dan (danceratopz): Otherwise, yeah, please put your thinking caps on and comment on the ACDE issue, if you have any other reservations or…

156
00:27:23.130 --> 00:27:25.829
dan (danceratopz): what we… what we need to do? Potus?

157
00:27:26.790 --> 00:27:41.660
Potuz: Yeah, so this is not something to take lightly, what Nico just said. One of the arguments to ship this EIP is to prevent having cached on clients, but clients will need a cache to deal with the fork.

158
